===Etymology===
From {{etyl|fr}} ''[[monolithe]]'', from {{etyl|la}} ''[[monolithus]]'' "consisting of a single stone", from {{etyl|grc}} [[μονόλιθος]] ''monotlithos'', from [[μόνος]] ''monos'' "single, alone" + [[λίθος]] ''lithos'' "stone".

===Noun===
{{wikipedia|monolith|monolith (1)}}
{{en-noun}}

# A large single block of [[stone]], used in [[architecture]] and [[sculpture]].
# Anything [[massive]], [[uniform]] and [[unmovable]].
# {{chemistry}} in [[chromatography]], a continuous [[stationary-phase]] [[cast#Verb|cast]] as a [[homogeneous]] [[column]] in a single piece

